parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tread Separation and Cracking of Mickey Thompson Tires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The tread separation and cracking of Mickey Thompson tires can cause loss of control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, resulting in potential harm to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: cracking around the sidewall and lugs

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inner-Liner Failure of Fuel Tank Causing Fuel Filter Clogging
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the inner-liner of the fuel tank can cause the fuel to mix with the liner material, leading to clogged fuel filters, which can result in engine stalling, loss of power, and potential accidents.
The failure of the front wheel hub can cause the wheel to separate from the vehicle, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The wheel suddenly comes loose or falls off while driving
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering becomes difficult or unstable
unusual noises or vibrations from the front wheel area.
